Source: smtpclient
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Jan Koester <jan.koester@tuxist.de>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), cmake (>= 3.10),
 libssl-dev, pkg-config
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: libsmtpclient
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: C++ SMTP client library
 A cross-platform C++ SMTP client library supporting TLS 1.3
 via OpenSSL. Provides three client classes for different
 security levels: OpportunisticSecureSMTPClient (STARTTLS),
 ForcedSecureSMTPClient (immediate SSL/TLS), and SmtpClient
 (plain). Includes both C++ and C interfaces.

Package: libsmtpclient-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: libsmtpclient (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}, libssl-dev
Description: C++ SMTP client library - development files
 A cross-platform C++ SMTP client library supporting TLS 1.3
 via OpenSSL.
 .
 This package contains the headers and CMake config files
 needed for development against libsmtpclient.
